name: BADE’E AL OUD – SUBLIME
top_notes: Lattafa Bade’e Al Oud Sublime is a luxurious and exotic fragrance that will surely captivate your senses. This unisex fragrance is a blend of woody, spicy and sweet notes to create a unique and seductive aroma. Top notes of lychee, rose and apple will give a sweet fruity initial sensation on your skin. At the heart of the fragrance, jasmine unfolds with a hint of ripe plum, giving you a spicy, oriental floral touch to your skin. The main notes of this fragrance are a combination of vanilla and patchouli, giving it a warm and sensual tone.

name: JAZZAB GOLD
top_notes:
Jazzab Gold fragrance by Ard Al Zaafaran is a creation dedicated to distinguished women. Despite the forbidden meeting of a black rose and a dark accord, Patchouli. Its addictive and sparkling wake reveals an intensely feminine sensuality, for a captivating moment.
This enigmatic creation is a sensual and mysterious elixir with bewitching hearts of black rose wrapped in a hint of spice.
Floral-oriental elixir, sensual and ardent revisiting the black rose. Moreover the top notes of Jazzab Gold consists of a bouquet of black rose as well as a slight hint of citrus. The heart note is spicy and floral with jasmine and peony. Musk and pink pepper in the base note. Amber, tonka and patchouli form the base.

Mugure – September 27, 2023
khamrah is a delicious scent, smells like it costs way way more than it actually does.
that nice gooey date + praline combination makes it so sensual & i just can’t stop smelling myself whenever i wear it.
tip: once you get it, spray some into the air or wherever to introduce oxygen into the bottle then allow it to macerate for around a month to truly enjoy the beauty that is khamrah.

This complex fragrance is reminiscent of a grand antique tapestry with its rich texture. A warm and dark note of musk envelops the composition like a veil of night and complements the sweet vanilla base notes. This is how morning roses turn into a magnificent night garden. A wonderful aroma that lingers long after midnight…
